						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold by one Vai[va]ḻippākkam-uḍaiyāṉ Perumānandi of Vēśālippāḍi, which was left in charge of the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of Kalaiyamaṅgalam who were to measure 2 <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice for offering to the god on the days of Tiruvādirai (every month), and to feed five persons in the temple with this consecrated food.</p>						

						</summary>
